== Yu Tung Court == Yu Tung Court ({{zh|t=è£æ±é¨}}) is a [[Home Ownership Scheme]] court in [[Tung Chung]], located near Fu Tung Estate and [[Tung Chung Station]]. Built on the [[Land reclamation in Hong Kong|reclaimed land]] of [[North Lantau New Town]] Phase 1 project, it is the first and the only HOS court in Tung Chung. It has a total of 5 blocks built in 1997, together with Yu Tung Estate.
{| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center" |- ! Name<ref>[http://www.housingauthority.gov.hk/en/interactivemap/court/0,,1-0-9_5726,00.html Hong Kong Housing Authority: Yu Tung Court]</ref> !! Type !! Completion |- | Heung Tung House|| rowspan="5" | Harmony 1 || rowspan="5" | 1997 |- | Hor Tung House |- | Hei Tung House |- | Kai Tung House |- | Sun Tung House |- |}
== Yat Tung Estate == [[Image:Yat Tung II Estate.jpg|thumb|Yat Tung (II) Estate]] [[File:Yat Tung Estate 1.jpg|thumb|Yat Tung Estate viewed across [[Tung Chung Bay]], with [[Sunset Peak]] in the background.]] [[File:Yat Tung Shopping Centre, Hong Kong.JPG|thumb|Yat Tung Shopping Centre]] [[File:HK YatTungArtWalk ManInNature.JPG|thumb|''Man in Nature'' created by Kan Tai-keung, one of the permanent displays of Yat Tung Artwalk.]] Yat Tung Estate ({{zh|t=é¸æ±é¨}}) is located in [[Tung Chung]]. It is divided into 'Yat Tung (I) Estate' ({{zh|t=é¸æ±(ä¸)é¨}}), completed in 2001 and comprising 13 blocks of Concord 1 and Harmony 1 types, and 'Yat Tung (II) Estate' ({{zh|t=é¸æ±(äº)é¨}}), completed in 2004 - 2005 and comprising 12 blocks of Harmony 1 and NCB types.<ref>[http://www.fso-tela.gov.hk/lib/locations_search_details.cfm?type=1&File_No=01016 Yat Tung Estate]</ref>
Residents of Yat Tung Estate have appealed to the government to extend the [[Tung Chung Line]] to Yat Tung to ease their transportation problems. Yat Tung Estate currently has 40,000 residents. They claimed that when they moved in 11 years ago, the [[Transport and Housing Bureau|Housing Bureau]]'s documents indicated a MTR station at the estate. The residents currently have to take a 10 minute bus journey to [[Tung Chung Station]].<ref>[http://paper.wenweipo.com/2011/05/25/HK1105250005.htm é¸æ±é¨å± æ°è¦æ±å»ºæ¸¯éµç«] ''Wen Wei Po''. 25 May 2011. {{zh-hk icon}}</ref>
